1924;;Isn't Life Wonderful;;American;;D. W. Griffith;;Carol Dempster, Neil Hamilton;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isn%27t_Life_Wonderful;;A family from Poland has been left homeless in the wake of World War I. They move to Germany and struggle to survive the conditions there, during the Great Inflation. Inga (Carol Dempster) is a Polish war orphan who has only accumulated a small amount of money from the rubble and hopes to marry Paul (Neil Hamilton). Weakened by poison gas, Paul begins to invest in Inga's future and he serves as their symbol of optimism.